%% F048 — Attack Graph: enriched kill-chains, positive-security intent coverage, and a DRY-RUN draft
%% that never enforces on its own (enforcement is the operator's explicit Policies apply).
sequenceDiagram
    actor Analyst
    participant UI as Console (Attack Graph)
    participant API as ThreatsRouter
    participant AG as asset-graph helpers
    participant Gen as threat_intent (generator)
    participant Eng as OPAEvaluator (dry-run key)
    participant Store as app.state.intent_drafts
    participant Pol as Policies (existing, gated)

    Analyst->>UI: Open Attack Graph (ns, range)
    UI->>API: GET /threats/attack-paths?ns=&cls=&range=
    API->>AG: _resolve_namespaces (scope + ns=all) + _latest_snapshots + _decision_counts
    AG-->>API: nodes + edges (+ real 24h decision history)
    API->>API: DFS kill-chains → enriched ThreatPath[] (status/dec from real audit data)
    API-->>UI: { paths worst-first, namespaces }
    UI-->>Analyst: ranked list · d3 kill-chain · inspector · stat strip

    Analyst->>UI: Define intended behaviour (toggles)
    UI->>API: POST /threats/intent-coverage {ns, cls, intent}
    API->>Gen: generate_intent_rego (DEFAULT-DENY, tighten-only)
    loop each path chokepoint
        API->>Eng: _evaluate_opa("dryrun:threat:cls", opa_input, rego)
        Eng-->>API: decision (block ⇒ path covered)
    end
    API-->>UI: { rego, covered[], residual[], covered_count/total }  %% eval-only, NO persistence

    Analyst->>UI: Apply intent (draft)
    UI->>API: POST /threats/intent-draft {ns, cls, intent}
    Note over API: require_admin + require_target_cluster (R2) + reject reserved scope
    API->>Store: stash draft (NON-enforcing; evaluator never reads it)
    API-->>UI: { draft_id, deeplink:/policies/catalog?intent_draft=, enforcement:"draft" }
    UI-->>Analyst: "Draft created · dry-run in Policies"

    Analyst->>Pol: (explicit) review + apply the generated rego
    Note over Pol: existing F-40 reserved-scope + F-51 apply_mode + R2 gates enforce here — the ONLY enforcement path
